{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how automated verification path for CLAUDE.local.md coverage will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f847919a5cfeb874c"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"automated verification path for CLAUDE.local.md coverage"},{"coaching":"Pin down canonical source for drift-guard delimited region with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fc780fc99f7979fa7"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"canonical source for drift-guard delimited region"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for file-ordering dependencies among sibling tickets — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f82524518cbf636a6"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"file-ordering dependencies among sibling tickets"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance criteria completeness and testability will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance criteria completeness and testability"},{"coaching":"Research prior art / OSS for SKILL.md front-matter schema vocabulary and provenance before building it custom.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fc81841bfa5d9c0b7"],"move_id":"2","move_name":"prior-art research","subject":"SKILL.md front-matter schema vocabulary and provenance"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":0,"dropped":25,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":5,"ran":true,"references":5,"resolved":1,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":4},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":3802,"file_impact":0,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":7,"edges":6,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"fail"},"P6":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":35,"verify_lint_abstained":35},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":975,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":2173},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":0,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":459.8,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":416551.9,"total_ms":417118.0,"verify_requests":14},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":false,"registry_unchanged":false,"sidecar_baseline":false,"within_window":false}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a structured checklist to 955c's change description template that enumerates each removed rule with its destination, and require a second reviewer to verify the mapping against AGENTS.md/docs before merging.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["955c AC2: 'Proving: for each removed rule, cite the AGENTS.md/docs location in the change description' — manual only","955c AC1: 'Proving: reviewer confirms' — manual only","CLAUDE.local.md is gitignored → CI cannot access it","Parent SC4 uses the same 'no guidance is lost' standard for both CLAUDE.md and CLAUDE.local.md without distinguishing automated vs. manual verification","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"SC4 ('no guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home') has no automated verification path for the CLAUDE.local.md half. 955c's AC relies solely on reviewer confirmation ('reviewer confirms') and a trending-to-zero rg check on locally removed patterns. Since CLAUDE.local.md is gitignored, CI cannot read it, and the content-completeness check ('for each removed rule, cite the AGENTS.md/docs location in the change description') is a manual code-review step with no enforcement. The parent success criterion is not measurably satisfied in the same terms (automated, reproducible) as the CLAUDE.md half.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f847919a5cfeb874c","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 955c-7a98-2485-4209 — Acceptance Criteria; parent SC4","norm_id":"n4766ab20eadf4211","priority":1.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A generally-applicable rule in CLAUDE.local.md (e.g., a project-specific quality gate added locally) is removed as 'local content' but has no AGENTS.md/docs home because it was never in CLAUDE.md → undetected guidance loss","Reviewer skims change description without checking each removed rule against AGENTS.md → rule silently dropped"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In 955c, produce an explicit removal manifest (a table: removed rule | new home | verified by) as part of the change description, and cross-reference it against 6642's AGENTS.md content in the same review. This is the closest achievable substitute for automated verification given the gitignored nature of the file.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the canonical-source ambiguity between 064f and 073d: either (a) add docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md to 073d's scope as the single aggregated source, or (b) commit 064f to a specific file list and update the drift-guard to compare multiple delimited regions with named sources.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["064f de-risking: 'natural candidate: docs/ticket-model.md plus the workflow loop authored in S1, or a dedicated docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md'","073d refined plan: content split across docs/ticket-model.md + docs/concurrency.md I4a + docs/event-schema.md + docs/user-guide.md","'S1' is a dangling label not resolvable to any named child in the sibling roster","064f AC: 'the drift-guard test compares the DELIMITED rebar-usage region … and fails when it diverges from the canonical source' — requires one canonical source","container pairing: parent + 064f-0484-2795-4ac7/073d-51d8-3e58-4b14/1d75-89cb-f37e-482e/46f8-cd08-7bf5-4508/5b01-add0-e970-44bd/6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4/955c-7a98-2485-4209"],"finding":"The canonical source file for 064f's drift-guard delimited region is unresolved: the de-risking text offers 'docs/ticket-model.md plus the workflow loop authored in S1, or a dedicated docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md' as alternatives but does not commit to one. 073d's refined plan scatters content across four separate doc files (docs/ticket-model.md, docs/concurrency.md, docs/event-schema.md, docs/user-guide.md); none of these individually contains all the 'portable rebar-usage' prose that the drift-guard needs to compare byte-for-byte. Without a single canonical source file, 064f's test cannot be implemented as designed (byte-identical delimited region), and 073d has no obligation to produce that single source. This is a partial-without-remainder gap: 064f covers AC3 only IF a single consolidated source exists, but no child commits to producing one.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc780fc99f7979fa7","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 064f-0484-2795-4ac7 — De-risking results / Revised AC; child 073d-51d8-3e58-4b14 — Refined plan","norm_id":"n352202c3bcbeb2e9","priority":0.5211,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["064f implementer picks docs/ticket-model.md as the source but the workflow-loop content lives in docs/user-guide.md → delimited block is incomplete → drift-guard silently allows divergence on omitted sections","073d implementer produces no docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md because it is not in 073d's scope → 064f implementer must create it themselves, potentially duplicating 073d content → the drift problem recurs in a different form","'S1' workflow loop never materializes as a doc section → template carries a delimited region with no authoritative counterpart → drift-guard test cannot be written"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md to 073d's scope as a thin aggregation file (just assembles the portable rebar-usage sections with include-markers); update 064f to treat that file as the sole canonical source for the drift-guard byte comparison. This mirrors how test_skill_shared_sync.py treats shared/ today.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AGENTS.md: 1d75-89cb-f37e-482e & 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4 (no ordering edge)"],"finding":"Sibling tickets touch the same file(s) with no ordering edge.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f82524518cbf636a6","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"na0177dc3af65d74f","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a depends_on/blocks edge to serialize, or partition the file ownership.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the canonical SKILL.md front-matter schema (required keys, optional keys, value constraints) in the plan or reference an authoritative external spec, so an executor generalizing the example skills knows exactly what structure to produce.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard) but are de-branded and generalized.'","rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md front-matter: `description:` only, no `name:` key","rebar-implement/SKILL.md front-matter: `name: rebar-implement` + `description:`","No section in the plan defines the SKILL.md schema vocabulary (required/optional keys, permitted values, order)"],"finding":"The plan claims SKILL.md is 'a cross-provider open standard' and directs de-branding of existing skills to that format, but the SKILL.md front-matter schema vocabulary is never defined: which keys are required, optional, or forbidden. Evidence: `rebar-implement/SKILL.md` has both `name` and `description` in front-matter; `rebar-brainstorm/SKILL.md` has only `description` (no `name`); `rebar-debug/SKILL.md` and `rebar-janitor/SKILL.md` include `name`. An executor generalizing and de-branding the skills cannot determine the correct canonical front-matter structure.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc81841bfa5d9c0b7","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (design session), AC3 / examples/claude-skills/*/SKILL.md","norm_id":"n09c7aa3a4abdeb12","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor generalizing the skills adds or omits a `name:` key inconsistently, breaking provider-specific skill-discovery that depends on front-matter parsing.","A cross-vendor harness that reads SKILL.md front-matter fails to discover skills whose front-matter is malformed relative to the 'standard' — but neither the executor nor the reviewer can check against an unspecified schema."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a 'SKILL.md schema' subsection under Scope (or a child story) that enumerates: required front-matter keys (e.g. `name`, `description`), optional keys, and any constraints — and cites the governing spec URL if the Agentic AI Foundation publishes one.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] AC3: Name the specific authoritative source file (e.g., `docs/using-rebar.md`) the template must track and define what 'in sync' means (e.g., 'all headings in the authoritative source appear in the template with matching content') so the drift-guard test is unambiguously implementable.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' — 'authoritative source' is never named (a specific docs/ file? the root AGENTS.md? a section thereof?)","'in sync' is undefined — identical content, key-section match, subset inclusion, or something else?","The proving command is only `make test` with no indication of which test file or assertion implements the drift check"],"finding":"The 'drift-guard test' in AC3 is underspecified: neither the authoritative source the template must track nor the definition of 'in sync' is stated, so an executor cannot write or validate the test without guessing.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6bc91ca91fb14c10","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3: `templates/AGENTS.md` drift-guard test","norm_id":"n87369632408f2e04","priority":0.134,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An agent writes a test that compares the full files byte-for-byte, but the intent was to track only the 'how to drive rebar' section — the test is wrong but appears to pass the stated AC.","An agent writes a test that checks a checksum of the template against AGENTS.md root, but the template should track a docs/ sub-file — drift goes undetected."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add to AC3: 'The drift-guard test (e.g., `tests/test_template_drift.py`) asserts that every H2 section present in `docs/using-rebar.md` appears verbatim (or via include) in `templates/AGENTS.md`; `make test` runs this check as part of the standard suite.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Success Criteria: Make the 'no guidance lost' criterion deterministic — e.g., add a migration checklist artifact (a structured inventory of every substantive rule in the current CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md, with a 'destination' column) that is committed alongside the changes and reviewed in the closing PR, making completeness auditable.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["No proving command is given for this criterion, unlike AC2 and AC4.","'Every rule removed … has an authoritative home' requires human judgment about semantic equivalence, not a machine-checkable assertion.","ABSENCE: no checklist, diff, or inventory mechanism is described that an agent could execute to verify completeness."],"finding":"The success criterion 'No guidance is lost in the move' is not deterministically evaluable — there is no observable artifact, command, or check that could verify completeness of content migration.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa975434b4dbe5503","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria — 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","norm_id":"nb2ab555f79526f0e","priority":0.1375,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A rule from CLAUDE.md is silently dropped during the move; nothing in the CI or test suite catches it because there is no inventory or diff-based check."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add to Success Criteria: 'A migration inventory (`docs/migration-inventory.md`) lists every distinct rule from `CLAUDE.md` and `CLAUDE.local.md` with its destination file; the closing PR includes this artifact as evidence of completeness. CI may optionally diff the inventory against the new files.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend AC3's verify step) that checks `.codex` and `.agents` shim files are updated and that the repo-wide reference sweep is complete (e.g., `rg -l 'CLAUDE.md' . | grep -v CLAUDE.md | wc -l` returns 0 or a named list is confirmed clean).","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope: 'In: the root guidance files, docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content, the .codex/.agents shims, examples/ skills, a client template + drift test, and a repo-wide reference sweep.'","None of the four ACs mention .codex, .agents shims, or a reference sweep."],"finding":"The Scope section names '.codex/.agents shims' and a 'repo-wide reference sweep' as in-scope deliverables, but no Acceptance Criterion covers them. An implementer who completes all ACs could leave shim files broken or stale references unremediated.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f82c437d73a642aef","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In: … `.codex`/`.agents` shims … and a repo-wide reference sweep'); Acceptance Criteria (all four ACs)","norm_id":"n0d170ba4752900f1","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer passes all ACs but leaves .codex/config.toml pointing at the old CLAUDE.md path, or stale references to 'examples/claude-skills' survive outside the paths checked by AC3."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC that verifies at least one key docs/ home exists (e.g., `test -f docs/agent-guidance.md` or equivalent) and that CLAUDE.md line count is within the stated target (e.g., `wc -l CLAUDE.md | awk '$1 <= 200'`).","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Key Insight: 'push the portable rebar-usage guidance into docs/ as the single source of truth, and have thin, audience-specific files point at it.'","AC1 verify: 'test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md' — tests only root file presence and pointer, not docs/ content.","No AC names any docs/ file or checks that content was moved there."],"finding":"The docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content are declared both in Scope ('In: docs/ homes for CLAUDE.md-native content') and as the single source of truth in Key Insight, but no AC verifies that any docs/ file was actually created or updated. The only migration-completeness check (AC1) only confirms AGENTS.md exists and CLAUDE.md references it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb0326e5d7b49be1e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section; Key Insight section; Acceptance Criteria (AC1)","norm_id":"n3a62ff1fdc3a96aa","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["AGENTS.md passes the AC1 check but duplicates content that was supposed to live in docs/, because no AC required the docs/ move."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a line-count assertion to AC1's proving step (e.g., `wc -l AGENTS.md | awk '$1 <= 200 {exit 0} {exit 1}'`) so the leanness target is machine-verifiable.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Success Criteria: 'The root guidance file is lean (target ≤ ~200 lines) and duplicates no doc that already has an authoritative version.'","No AC includes a line-count check."],"finding":"The Success Criteria state a target of ≤~200 lines for the root guidance file, but no AC measures or enforces this constraint, so the leanness goal is unverifiable at merge time.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd3431b56c6c0eb36","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria ('The root guidance file is lean (target ≤ ~200 lines)'); Acceptance Criteria (all four ACs)","norm_id":"n1221cde417cdc96f","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["AGENTS.md is created but grows to 400 lines by incorporating CLAUDE.md content wholesale; all ACs still pass."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"wc -l AGENTS.md | awk '$1 <= 200 {exit 0} {exit 1}'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the authoritative source in AC2 by name (e.g., 'drift-guard test keeps templates/AGENTS.md in sync with `docs/<filename>.md`') to eliminate implementer ambiguity.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1","COH"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2: 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' — 'the authoritative source' is not named.","Key Insight: 'push the portable rebar-usage guidance into docs/ as the single source of truth'.","Locked Decisions: 'AGENTS.md becomes the canonical root file'."],"finding":"AC2 requires a drift-guard test that keeps templates/AGENTS.md 'in sync with the authoritative source', but the AC text never identifies what the authoritative source is. Key Insight says docs/ is the SoT; Locked Decisions say AGENTS.md is the canonical root file. An implementer must guess which artifact the drift test should compare against.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb387d99fc4df4311","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, AC2 ('a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'); Key Insight; Locked Decisions","norm_id":"naee78b21a9842718","priority":0.1375,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["One implementer writes the drift test comparing templates/AGENTS.md against docs/agent-guidance.md; another compares it against the root AGENTS.md. The tests pass independently but guard against different things."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a verify step (or extend AC1) that confirms CLAUDE.md and CLAUDE.local.md no longer contain content that is now authoritative in AGENTS.md/docs/, e.g., by checking line count or asserting absence of specific section headers known to duplicate docs/.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Success Criteria: 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/.'","AC1 verify: 'test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md' — only confirms AGENTS.md exists and CLAUDE.md has the pointer; does not confirm duplicated content was removed from CLAUDE.md or CLAUDE.local.md.","AC3 verify addresses example skills rename only."],"finding":"The Success Criteria's fourth bullet ('No guidance is lost — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home') states a migration completeness requirement, but no AC verifies the removal side: that CLAUDE.md and CLAUDE.local.md were actually trimmed of duplicated content.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1b6c92ceb0a330a6","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria (fourth bullet); Acceptance Criteria (AC1)","norm_id":"naf0477e1f08b6328","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["CLAUDE.md retains all 665 lines plus the @AGENTS.md pointer at the top; all ACs pass but the duplication and bloat remain entirely intact."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the target directory name for `examples/claude-skills/` explicitly in the plan, add a redirect/alias notice or CHANGELOG entry for external consumers, and document a back-out procedure (e.g., `git revert` range or re-rename script).","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: '`rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0' sweeps internal references only","The new directory name is absent from the plan entirely","No rollback step or git-mv preservation strategy is mentioned","Scope says 'repo-wide reference sweep' but scope boundary is internal-only"],"finding":"The rename of `examples/claude-skills/` to a provider-neutral directory is treated as incidental — the new target name is never stated in the plan, and no rollback/back-out plan is provided for the destructive rename. External consumers (forks, bookmarks, external documentation referencing the old path) are not addressed.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f472cde523f3d7edd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, item 3 / Scope section","norm_id":"ncecaccef401b46bf","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A downstream user or CI pipeline that references `examples/claude-skills/` by URL or relative path breaks silently after merge with no migration notice","If the new name proves wrong, reverting requires re-renaming and re-sweeping all references with no documented procedure"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a plan section: 'Rename `examples/claude-skills/` → `examples/skills/` (or chosen name). Back-out: `git mv examples/skills examples/claude-skills && git commit`. External notice: add a one-release deprecation shim (symlink or README redirect) so prior references continue to resolve.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit rollback plan for the CLAUDE.md truncation (e.g., preserve the original as `CLAUDE.md.bak` or a tagged commit, and document how to restore it if `@AGENTS.md` import verification fails).","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import' — no fallback if import fails","AC2 proves the pointer exists but not that Claude Code resolves it correctly","No rollback step (e.g., 'if @AGENTS.md import is broken, restore CLAUDE.md from tag X') is described"],"finding":"The plan truncates `CLAUDE.md` from 665 lines to a thin `@AGENTS.md` pointer, but provides no rollback/back-out plan if the `@AGENTS.md` import mechanism fails or is not supported as expected in Claude Code.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbeae580ebaa2c551","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions / Acceptance Criteria item 2","norm_id":"ncde89a8cbc140f4a","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code silently ignores or misparses the @AGENTS.md directive, causing all Claude Code sessions to run with near-zero guidance until the issue is noticed","A Claude Code version update changes import semantics, making the thin pointer ineffective"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Tag the pre-migration commit and document in the story: 'Rollback: `git checkout <pre-migration-tag> -- CLAUDE.md` restores the full file. Verify @AGENTS.md import works by running a Claude Code session and confirming it reads the rebar-internal rules before closing the old file.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a committed ADR (e.g., `docs/adr/0001-agents-md-canonical-guidance.md`) recording the decision to adopt AGENTS.md as the cross-vendor standard, the alternatives considered, and the rationale.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'See the design-of-record session log for the full research basis' — session log is not a committed repo artifact","No ADR file is mentioned in Scope or Acceptance Criteria","The AGENTS.md standard adoption is described as a 'locked decision' but without a durable in-repo record"],"finding":"No ADR or committed documentation captures the architectural decision to adopt AGENTS.md as the cross-vendor canonical standard. The plan references a 'design-of-record session log' but session logs are ephemeral/external; no doc is committed to the repo.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"feb7f716d17003685","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section / Locked decisions","norm_id":"n7875cbe5b6391a0e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future contributor questions why AGENTS.md was chosen over CLAUDE.md or a different convention and finds no in-repo answer","The session log link rots, leaving no rationale for the architectural choice"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly specify the end-state for `CLAUDE.local.md` in the plan (deleted, thinned to local-only content, or converted to a thin pointer) and add an AC or scope item to verify it.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'CLAUDE.local.md mixes genuinely machine/operator-local content with generally-applicable project rules copied from CLAUDE.md' — problem stated","No AC, no Scope item, and no Success Criterion addresses what happens to CLAUDE.local.md post-migration","Scope says 'root guidance files' are in-scope but doesn't enumerate CLAUDE.local.md's outcome"],"finding":"`CLAUDE.local.md` is identified as problematic in Context but its end-state after migration is never specified — the plan does not say whether it is deleted, thinned, or left unchanged. Any existing references to it in onboarding docs or tooling will either strand or go stale.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3d02965d783c9409","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section / Scope section","norm_id":"n629d2cbefa9d412b","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["After migration, CLAUDE.local.md still contains the duplicated rules, making the de-duplication incomplete","Onboarding docs that reference CLAUDE.local.md point at a stale or restructured file with no update"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Scope: 'CLAUDE.local.md is thinned to machine/operator-local content only (worktree paths, venv locations, personal tokens); all generally-applicable rules are removed and replaced with a comment pointing to AGENTS.md.' Add AC: `rg -c 'generally-applicable' CLAUDE.local.md` returns 0.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a smoke-test or cite official Claude Code documentation confirming that a bare `@AGENTS.md` line in CLAUDE.md is resolved as an include/import (not ignored), or include a RED fixture that verifies Claude Code loads the content from AGENTS.md.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'","AC proving step only checks string presence (`rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`), not that Claude Code resolves the import at runtime","No cited Claude Code documentation for @-import resolution; no spike or fixture validating end-to-end pickup"],"finding":"The plan asserts that a one-line `@AGENTS.md` import in CLAUDE.md will cause Claude Code to load AGENTS.md content, but no empirical probe, cited documentation, or RED test is included to verify that Claude Code actually resolves this `@`-import syntax rather than treating it as a comment.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fddd0dcbb79c7f975","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (1) / Acceptance Criteria — `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`","norm_id":"n0f83889f11132ee6","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code treats the @AGENTS.md line as a comment and never loads AGENTS.md, silently losing all dev guidance for Claude Code users — the primary consumer of the old CLAUDE.md"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Either (a) cite the Claude Code docs URL confirming @-file import syntax and add it to the plan, or (b) add an AC step: open Claude Code in the repo and confirm via `/context` or equivalent that AGENTS.md content appears in the active context window — document the result as a one-time empirical proof.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"no","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a deliverable to the plan: commit a concise ADR (e.g., `docs/adr/001-agents-md-migration.md`) capturing the decision to migrate to AGENTS.md as canonical, the pointer-chain pattern, the provider matrix rationale, and the client-template/drift-guard contract.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'See the design-of-record session log for the full research basis (AGENTS.md governance, provider matrix, OSS patterns, anti-patterns)'","No deliverable in Scope, Success Criteria, or AC specifies creating a committed ADR or design doc capturing the migration decision","Session logs are ephemeral and not co-located with the code for future maintainers"],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel architectural pattern (provider-neutral AGENTS.md canonical file, CLAUDE.md pointer chain, client template with drift guard) whose design rationale lives only in an external session log, not in a committed, durable ADR or design doc in the repo.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7e1c6de10e59aae1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context / Locked decisions / Success Criteria","norm_id":"n80ff9d045237b98c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Six months later, a maintainer wonders why CLAUDE.md is a one-liner, why templates/AGENTS.md exists, or whether to add a new provider shim — the rationale is unreachable without the session log link, which may be stale or inaccessible"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create `docs/adr/001-agents-md-migration.md` summarizing: (1) problem (CLAUDE.md bloat, Claude-lock), (2) decision (AGENTS.md canonical + thin CLAUDE.md pointer + client template), (3) provider support evidence, (4) rejected alternatives, (5) drift-guard contract. Reference it from AGENTS.md itself.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or proving command) that verifies content completeness of the migration — e.g., a checklist of named rules/sections with their new homes, or a script that diffs removed CLAUDE.md lines against `docs/` and `AGENTS.md` to confirm each has a corresponding entry.","cohort":["E3","F4"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Success criterion: 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/'","ABSENCE: No AC entry and no proving command corresponds to content-completeness of the migration.","Existing ACs test `test -f AGENTS.md`, `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`, `test -f templates/AGENTS.md && make test`, and example-rename — none verify rule-level completeness."],"finding":"The success criterion 'No guidance is lost in the move — every rule removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md has an authoritative home in AGENTS.md or docs/' has no end-state-observable proof or AC proving command. The existing ACs verify file existence and reference counts but cannot confirm that every removed rule was re-homed.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f86c281189f0cb84f","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria (4th bullet) and Acceptance Criteria section","norm_id":"ndca73f334f922316","priority":0.11,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A rule (e.g., the Gerrit split-remote policy) is deleted from CLAUDE.md during migration but not written into AGENTS.md or docs/; the gap is invisible to all ACs.","An implementer treats 'thin pointer' as license to drop content without documenting where it moved."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add an AC entry such as: '[ ] A migration manifest (docs/migration-manifest.md or inline table) enumerates every section removed from CLAUDE.md/CLAUDE.local.md and its new canonical location; `make test` or a dedicated script verifies each listed target path exists.' This makes completeness machine-checkable.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or a `make lint` check) that enforces the ≤ ~200-line target for `AGENTS.md`, e.g., `proving: [ $(wc -l < AGENTS.md) -le 200 ]`.","cohort":["E3","F4"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Success criterion: 'The root guidance file is lean (target ≤ ~200 lines) and duplicates no doc that already has an authoritative version.'","ABSENCE: No AC bullet and no proving command (e.g., `wc -l AGENTS.md`) corresponds to this criterion."],"finding":"The success criterion targeting AGENTS.md line-count ('target ≤ ~200 lines') has no corresponding AC entry and no proving command, leaving it un-verifiable at story close.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd6700e59984ba9ce","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Success Criteria (2nd bullet)","norm_id":"n9c4ac704d7fd8061","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["AGENTS.md grows to 350 lines during implementation; the target is missed but every AC still passes.","Drift from later PRs goes unnoticed because there is no automated line-count gate."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Append to the AC section: '[ ] `AGENTS.md` is ≤ 200 lines. Proving: `[ $(wc -l < AGENTS.md) -le 200 ] && echo ok`'. Optionally add a lint rule so CI enforces it going forward.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly mark the main migration children (interfaith-proud-dromedary, enormous-new-kusimanse, metal-fusible-unicorn) as evidence-gated on eastbound-bald-raptors closing with a confirmed positive result, so that a failed or qualified spike result triggers a plan revision before migration work begins.","cohort":["G5"],"criteria":["G5"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["eastbound-bald-raptors is listed alongside 6 other children with no stated ordering or dependency constraint","The spike's purpose — 'verify Claude Code loads AGENTS.md via a @AGENTS.md import' — is foundational: the entire thin-CLAUDE.md strategy depends on this working","No 'blocked by eastbound-bald-raptors' annotation on interfaith-proud-dromedary or enormous-new-kusimanse"],"finding":"The spike (eastbound-bald-raptors) that verifies Claude Code's @AGENTS.md import behavior is listed as a peer of the main migration children, with no explicit evidence-gate documented: if the spike reveals the import mechanism does not work as assumed, the canonical AGENTS.md creation (interfaith-proud-dromedary) and content re-homing (enormous-new-kusimanse) may both need to be redesigned, creating substantial rework risk.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffd3d0e82a3b02068","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Decomposition State / child ticket list; Success Criteria section","norm_id":"n9dbfb42bf1e4e3ef","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Spike discovers @AGENTS.md import is not yet stable in Claude Code; migration work already landed in main requires a second rewrite pass.","Spike reveals Claude Code uses a different import syntax or loads AGENTS.md unconditionally without an import, changing the optimal CLAUDE.md shape."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Depends on: eastbound-bald-raptors (must close green)' annotation in the epic's Scope or AC section, and document a brief contingency note: 'If the spike finds @AGENTS.md import is unsupported or unreliable, revisit the thin-CLAUDE.md strategy before opening the migration children.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Before finalizing the migration architecture, verify (by citing official Claude Code documentation or running an empirical probe) that a bare `@AGENTS.md` line in `CLAUDE.md` causes Claude Code to load and apply AGENTS.md's content, and add either a citation or a spike result as evidence in the plan.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'","AC proving step: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` — checks string presence only, not runtime resolution by Claude Code","No citation of official Claude Code documentation confirming @-file import syntax","No spike, fixture, or empirical test that Claude Code loads AGENTS.md content when CLAUDE.md contains this line"],"finding":"The core migration mechanism—a one-line `@AGENTS.md` import in `CLAUDE.md` causing Claude Code to load `AGENTS.md` content—is asserted but never grounded in cited documentation or an empirical probe. The AC proving step (`rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`) verifies only that the string exists, not that Claude Code resolves it as an include. If Claude Code does not honor this `@`-import syntax (treating it as a comment or unknown directive), all dev guidance silently vanishes for the current primary consumer, with no failing test to detect it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9297ef304ecc3dd4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (1); Acceptance Criteria — `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` proving step","norm_id":"nc2289fae9b9c2ef8","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code treats `@AGENTS.md` as a comment or unknown directive and never loads AGENTS.md, silently dropping all dev guidance (worktree flow, Gerrit remotes, gate protocols, module-size policy, Serena navigation) for every Claude Code session after migration.","The @-import syntax is valid but only for files in certain locations or with certain naming, requiring a different path or syntax to work correctly."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Either (a) add a link to the Claude Code docs page confirming @-file import syntax and note it in Locked Decisions, or (b) add a one-time empirical AC: 'In a live Claude Code session on this repo, run `/context` or equivalent and confirm AGENTS.md content appears in the active context window; record the result as a comment on this ticket.' If the mechanism is uncertain, the thin-pointer strategy should pivot to a `cp AGENTS.md CLAUDE.md` generation approach (generate CLAUDE.md from AGENTS.md at CI time) as a fallback that does not depend on import resolution.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"no","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the plan (or in a child story) exactly which file or section serves as the authoritative source for `templates/AGENTS.md` drift detection, and define the sync predicate (e.g., byte-identical to a generated extract, or structural: named sections must be present, or checksum of a specific docs/ page).","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: 'templates/AGENTS.md (client-usable, provider-neutral) exists and a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","The plan's Key Insight designates docs/ as 'the single source of truth' for portable rebar-usage guidance, but does not name which docs/ file(s) the template must track","The existing analogous test (test_skill_shared_sync.py) succeeds because it hardcodes the canonical path (`examples/claude-skills/shared/test-design.md`) and uses byte-identical comparison — the plan's template drift guard names neither","A client template cannot be byte-identical to an internal docs/ file (it must omit rebar-internal specifics per the Success Criteria), so the sync predicate cannot simply be byte-equality"],"finding":"The drift-guard test for `templates/AGENTS.md` (AC3) is mechanistically underspecified: the plan says the test 'keeps it in sync with the authoritative source' but neither names the authoritative source nor defines what 'in sync' means. Without these two definitions, an implementer cannot write a deterministic, correct test — the comparison subject and the comparison predicate are both unresolved.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f677a7fdb0b6840bd","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3: 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","norm_id":"n50412ad28d4a0655","priority":0.1675,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Implementer writes a test that checks `templates/AGENTS.md` is non-empty and `make test` passes trivially, but the template drifts from the real guidance with no detection.","Implementer uses byte-identical comparison but the template legitimately differs from the source (client-facing vs. rebar-internal content), causing constant false failures.","Two implementers independently write tests against different candidate authoritative sources (e.g., AGENTS.md root vs. a specific docs/ file), producing inconsistent behavior."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"If the template is a curated subset of AGENTS.md (rebar-internal sections stripped), the authoritative source is AGENTS.md itself and the sync predicate is 'all non-internal-dev sections from AGENTS.md appear verbatim in the template.' The test can extract those sections by heading and compare. Document this extraction boundary explicitly in the plan so the implementer has a deterministic specification.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and cite the exact Claude Code syntax for importing/including AGENTS.md content from CLAUDE.md (e.g., check whether `@AGENTS.md` is valid, or whether it requires a different form such as an `additionalInstructions` setting or `@file:AGENTS.md` directive), and add a runtime-observable proving command to AC2 that confirms the import is resolved — not just that the text is present.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'","AC2 proving command: `test -f AGENTS.md && rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` — validates text presence, not import resolution","Absence: no cited Claude Code documentation for @AGENTS.md import syntax, no spike result, no fallback if unsupported"],"finding":"The plan's central CLAUDE.md bridging mechanism — 'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import' — is an unverified capability assertion about Claude Code's file-import syntax. The AC2 proving command (`rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`) only verifies the text is present, not that Claude Code resolves the import. If this syntax is unsupported or requires a different form (e.g. a specific front-matter `@file` directive, a `.claude/settings.json` `additionalInstructions` entry, or a `@path/to/AGENTS.md` prefix), Claude Code users — the primary audience — silently lose all guidance from AGENTS.md.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3c08b84db4e366fb","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section / Locked decisions (1) / AC2 proving command","norm_id":"nba697c251e8ae8d3","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code does not implement `@AGENTS.md` as a file-import directive (or requires a different syntax/location), so CLAUDE.md contains a one-line pointer that Claude Code ignores as literal text — the entire rebar dev guidance goes missing for Claude Code sessions.","A future Claude Code update changes the import syntax, and the CLAUDE.md pointer silently stops working with no test catching the regression."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a smoke-test or acceptance check that runs Claude Code with the thin CLAUDE.md in a controlled context and verifies the AGENTS.md content is visible to the session (or cite the specific Claude Code docs section that defines this import syntax). If the syntax is unconfirmed, promote the already-referenced spike to a prerequisite gate (must pass before the migration story is claimed), not a peer story.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"no","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Cite a verifiable source establishing SKILL.md as a cross-provider standard (e.g., an AAF spec, a multi-vendor adoption registry, or explicit support documentation from at least one non-Anthropic harness), or narrow the portability claim to 'readable by any harness that supports AGENTS.md/markdown instruction files' and document harness-specific invocation differences.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard) but are de-branded and generalized'","examples/claude-skills/README.md lines 1-2: 'This directory holds a small set of Claude Code skills' with a link to Claude Code docs","examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md line 65: 'CLAUDE.md / CLAUDE.local.md / CONTRIBUTING.md / docs/ in the repo root' — still Claude-specific prose","Absence: no citation or external reference establishing SKILL.md as a multi-vendor standard"],"finding":"The plan asserts that 'SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)' is the basis for keeping example skills in that format after de-branding, but no source, governance document, or adoption evidence is cited. The current SKILL.md files in `examples/claude-skills/` use Claude Code-specific YAML front-matter (`name:`, `description:` keys) and the README explicitly links to the Claude Code skills docs. Calling this format an 'open standard' is an unverified capability assertion: if other harnesses (Codex, Cursor, Copilot, etc.) do not discover or parse SKILL.md files, renaming the directory achieves branding change only, not actual cross-provider portability.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f26ae0c5e53816ddb","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Context section / Locked decisions (3) — 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard)'","norm_id":"na87fcdc46c7c5ada","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["The directory is renamed from claude-skills/ to agent-skills/ (or similar) and SKILL.md files are de-branded, but Codex/Cursor/Copilot have no mechanism to discover or execute SKILL.md-formatted instructions — the 'cross-provider' claim is cosmetic.","AC3 drift-guard test passes (template in sync) but the template itself still embeds Claude Code-specific invocation mechanics, defeating the portability goal."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify that Claude Code resolves a bare `@AGENTS.md` line in `CLAUDE.md` as a file import at session load time by citing the official Claude Code documentation URL for this syntax and/or running an empirical probe (e.g. `/context` output confirms AGENTS.md content is present), and record the result as evidence in the plan before committing the migration.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'","AC2 proving command checks only string presence, not runtime import resolution","No cited documentation for Claude Code @-file import syntax","No spike, fixture, or empirical probe of this capability in the plan","Evidence class: Unverified — the specific @-import surface has not been probed"],"finding":"The plan's central technical mechanism — a one-line `@AGENTS.md` import in `CLAUDE.md` that causes Claude Code to load `AGENTS.md` — is asserted but never verified against Claude Code's documented behavior. The AC proving step (`rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`) only confirms the string exists in the file; it does not verify that Claude Code resolves `@`-prefixed filenames as includes at runtime. No Claude Code documentation URL, no empirical probe, and no live test of the mechanism is cited in the plan.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0bb66f1fa2ef3115","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (1): 'a thin CLAUDE.md bridges Claude Code via a one-line @AGENTS.md import'; Acceptance Criteria #2 proving step: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md`","norm_id":"nb71f4aab71df05f0","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["Claude Code treats the `@AGENTS.md` line as a markdown comment or text fragment and never loads AGENTS.md, silently stripping all dev guidance from Claude Code sessions after migration with no failing test to detect it.","Claude Code supports `@file` imports in some contexts (e.g. in-prompt) but NOT in CLAUDE.md at file-load time — the mechanism differs by context."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Check the Claude Code docs at https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code (or `claude --help`) for the `@file` import directive in memory/context files. If confirmed, add the doc URL to the plan and update AC2's proving step to include a runtime verification (e.g. `claude -p 'print the first line of AGENTS.md' | grep expected-text`). If the syntax is NOT supported in CLAUDE.md file-load context, pivot to an alternative bridging mechanism (e.g. embedding a short summary in CLAUDE.md that explicitly instructs Claude Code to read AGENTS.md, or using a `#import` directive if one exists).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"no","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Cite a specification URL or vendor documentation confirming that SKILL.md is recognized as a cross-vendor format (not just a Claude Code convention), or narrow the claim to 'Claude Code–compatible, adaptable format' and update the renaming rationale accordingly.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-vendor open standard)'","examples/claude-skills/README.md: 'This directory holds a small set of Claude Code skills' — framed as Claude Code–specific","examples/claude-skills/README.md: 'copy the skill's directory into your Claude Code skills location and invoke it by its name — see the Claude Code skills documentation'","No URL, spec, or governance reference for SKILL.md as a cross-vendor standard anywhere in the plan or repo","Evidence class: Unverified — the cross-vendor status of SKILL.md has not been probed against any vendor's documentation"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-vendor open standard)' to justify the provider-neutral rename of `examples/claude-skills/`. The repo's own `examples/claude-skills/README.md` describes SKILL.md as a Claude Code–specific construct; no external governance body, specification URL, or evidence of other vendors adopting SKILL.md is cited anywhere in the plan or repo.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0dd7560cf9791743","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Locked decisions (3): 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-vendor open standard)'","norm_id":"n8d74fb79fec27ccf","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["The plan's rename to 'provider-neutral examples/' is done on the premise that SKILL.md is cross-vendor, but Codex/Cursor/Copilot do not recognize SKILL.md as a skills-invocation format — the examples become harder to discover/use without the Claude Code framing, with no actual cross-provider benefit.","A contributor copies a SKILL.md to Cursor/Codex expecting it to be invoked by name, finds it silently ignored, and raises a support issue."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In AC3, name the authoritative source for `templates/AGENTS.md` (e.g., a specific `docs/` page or a defined section of `AGENTS.md`) and define what 'in sync' means (e.g., 'the template's portable-guidance sections match the corresponding sections of `docs/rebar-for-clients.md` byte-for-byte').","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","No plan section names the authoritative source for templates/AGENTS.md","No plan section defines what 'in sync' means (byte-identical? section-by-section subset? key-phrase presence?)","Existing drift-guard in repo (scripts/check_server_manifest.py) defines its authoritative source (MCP_ENV_VARS) and its sync predicate (exact set equality) — this plan omits the equivalent for the new test"],"finding":"AC3 requires a 'drift-guard test keeps [templates/AGENTS.md] in sync with the authoritative source' but neither the authoritative source nor the definition of 'in sync' is stated anywhere in the plan. An executor cannot write a deterministic, failing-first test without knowing (a) which file/section is the authoritative source and (b) what relationship constitutes drift.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f10d196d7c157ae34","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria, AC3: 'a drift-guard test keeps it in sync with the authoritative source'","norm_id":"nf4dca61907733437","priority":0.1375,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor writes the drift-guard test as a byte-equality check against AGENTS.md root, which breaks every time a rebar-internal section is updated, defeating the client-template isolation goal.","An executor writes a loose keyword-presence check that never actually catches real drift, making the AC vacuously pass."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Amend AC3 to: 'a drift-guard test asserts that `templates/AGENTS.md` is byte-identical to the output of `scripts/render_client_template.py` (which extracts the portable sections from `docs/<authoritative-doc>.md`)' — or whichever concrete predicate is chosen.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly list updating all `CLAUDE.md`/`CLAUDE.local.md` filename references inside `examples/claude-skills/*/SKILL.md` and supporting phase files (e.g. `rebar-janitor/phases/discovery.md`) to `AGENTS.md` as a named deliverable in the Scope or a child story, and add a proving command to AC4 that verifies no `CLAUDE.md` guidance-discovery reference survives in the skills directory.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["rebar-implement/SKILL.md line 65: '**`CLAUDE.md` / `CLAUDE.local.md` / `CONTRIBUTING.md` / `docs/`** in the repo root — the authoritative source'","rebar-janitor/phases/discovery.md line 10: 'Read the repo's agent guidance (`CLAUDE.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`)'","Plan text: 'Example skills stay in the SKILL.md format (now a cross-provider open standard) but are de-branded and generalized' — no mention of updating internal CLAUDE.md references","AC4 proving command only checks that `rg -l 'examples/claude-skills' . | wc -l` returns 0 (directory rename), not that `CLAUDE.md` references inside skills are also updated"],"finding":"The plan directs de-branding of the example skills but does not call out that the skills' own instruction text hard-codes `CLAUDE.md`/`CLAUDE.local.md` by name as the file to read for project rules — an instruction-locality antipattern that survives the migration unless explicitly listed for remediation. After the migration, agents following the skills would look for `CLAUDE.md` (the deprecated thin pointer) rather than `AGENTS.md` (the new canonical file).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2adbb94ccff0bcac","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope ('examples/ skills'), examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md line 65, examples/claude-skills/rebar-janitor/phases/discovery.md line 10","norm_id":"n05bcf593fb74db20","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A client project copying the de-branded skills gets agents that look for `CLAUDE.md` — which won't exist if the client follows the plan's template and only creates `AGENTS.md`.","After migration in rebar itself, `CLAUDE.md` becomes a thin one-liner; agents following the skill would load only that one line instead of the full `AGENTS.md` guidance, silently degrading instruction quality."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to AC4: `rg -l 'CLAUDE\\.md' examples/ | wc -l` returns 0 (or only matches that refer to the file as a historical artifact, not as the live guidance source to read). Update the two cited lines to name 