two 'stowaways' (the LLM-agent-operations paragraph → docs/llm-framework.md; the completion-verification close-gate blockquote → docs/plan-review-gate.md), but this is doc-editing work functionally identical to 073d's scope ('Re-home CLAUDE.md-native content into authoritative docs'). Both stories write to docs/ without an explicit coordination protocol, and neither lists the other as a dependency for the doc-writing subtask. If both are implemented concurrently, the same target files (llm-framework.md, plan-review-gate.md) may be edited in parallel, producing merge conflicts or duplicated sections.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd168dba2f5a4307d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6642-814b-8bc5-4ff4 — De-risking results ('Two stowaways'); child 073d-51d8-3e58-4b14 — Scope","norm_id":"nc2acad36cca08abf","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["073d implementer, seeing 'session logs' and 'gate protocols' as native content, also edits plan-review-gate.md; 6642 implementer independently edits the same file → conflicting patches at review time","6642 implementer defers stowaway re-homing assuming 073d will do it; 073d implementer doesn't know about stowaways → stowaways not re-homed → AGENTS.md pointers point to non-existent sections"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Move the two stowaway re-homes into 073d's scope (it is the canonical re-homing story) and add a note in 6642 that it depends on 073d for those doc sections existing, consistent with the already-stated 'depends on re-home story' dependency.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_c